\[(1+\frac{\Delta B}{B})^{-1}=1-\frac{\Delta B}{B}+(\frac{\Delta B}{B})^{2}-( \frac{\Delta B}{B})^{3}+\ldots\approx 1-\frac{\Delta B}{B}\]

**Hence, minimum** \(Z\!\!\approx\!\frac{A}{B}(1-\frac{\Delta A}{A})(1-\frac{\Delta B}{B})=\!\frac{ A}{B}(1-\frac{\Delta A}{A}-\frac{\Delta B}{B}+\frac{\Delta A}{A}\frac{\Delta B}{B})\)

\(\Delta Z\!=\!\gamma_{2}\ (\text{maximum}\ Z-\text{minimum}\ Z)=\frac{A}{B}( \frac{\Delta A}{A}+\frac{\Delta B}{B})\)

**Dividing throughout by** \(Z\)**, we have**

\[\frac{\Delta Z}{Z}=\frac{\frac{A\Delta A}{B}\frac{\Delta A}{A}\frac{\Delta B }{Z}}{Z}=\frac{\frac{A\Delta A}{B}\frac{\Delta A}{A}\frac{\Delta B}{B}}{\frac {\Delta B}{B}}\]

\[\frac{\Delta Z}{Z}=\frac{\Delta A}{A}+\frac{\Delta B}{B}\]

**Hence, for division of quantities, the fractional uncertainty is also given by the** _sum_ **of the fractional uncertainties of the quantities.**

